  "text": "Blood lipids were measured enzymatically with the commercially available reagents (Cholesterol/HP, cat. no. 816302, and Triglycerides/GPO, cat. no. 816370, both from the Boehringer Mannheim). HDL cholesterol was measured in the clear supernatant after precipitating the other lipoproteins with heparin and MnCl 2 (1.3 g/L and 0.046 mol/L, resp.) and removing excess Mn 2+ by precipitation with NaHCO 3 . Fasting glucose was measured using the Glucose Standard Assay (Sigma Chemical, St. Louis) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
